And if there's only one even amongst us who do not have Jesus as their Savior today, come to Him and tell Him, Jesus, I take you as my Savior, as my shield, as my God.

34:23.106 --> 34:29.255
history is filled with men and women who gave it all to God.

34:30.617 --> 34:34.643
They surrendered their lives, their destiny and their future.

34:35.444 --> 34:42.415
He blessed them, multiplied them, and accomplished great wonders through them.

34:43.296 --> 34:48.023
Our God is a wonder-working God.

34:50.146 --> 34:52.530
He will do wonders in your life.

34:52.834 --> 34:53.615
if you let them.

34:54.716 --> 34:57.400
Have a happy new year and may God bless you.

34:57.820 --> 34:59.322
This bar has for prayers.

35:03.087 --> 35:16.103
Thank you, Father, for giving us such an opportunity to meditate on your words, to get the encouragement, to get the peace that passes all understanding.

35:17.605 --> 35:21.810
Help us as we leave this auditorium that

35:22.626 --> 35:27.091
We decide to live a pure and dedicated life to you.

35:28.373 --> 35:46.514
Today, and leave tomorrow in your hands, be with each and every family, and give us all Lord a wonderful year filled with joy, happiness, and many people to come to know you as their Savior.

35:47.154 --> 35:50.258
Dismiss us, we pray, in Jesus' name, amen.

35:50.786 --> 35:51.891
The meeting is over.

35:51.932 --> 35:53.359
Thank you for listening to me.

35:54.203 --> 35:59.730
It's 12.15, and you still have time for any program you have.

